Setup

# Packages
library(tidyverse)
library(vegan)

# Directories
int.dir <- file.path("analyses", "7habitat","intermediate_data")

# Read Data
## Attributes
att_data <- readRDS(file.path(int.dir, "mpa_attributes_nmds_subset.Rds"))
  
## Kelp Fish Counts
kf_fish <- readRDS(file.path(int.dir, "species_matrix_kelp_fish_1620.Rds")) 

## Kelp Swath Counts
kf_swath <- readRDS(file.path(int.dir, "species_matrix_kelp_swath_1620.Rds"))

Fish Community

Species matrix for 2016-2020 average count per year.

# Get MPA attributes for MPAs in kelp species matrix 
kf_env <- att_data %>% 
  filter(name %in% kf_fish$name) 

# Save metadata df
kf_md <- kf_env %>% 
  select(name, region)

# Set up species matrix for vegan analyses
kf_fish[is.na(kf_fish)] <- 0
kf_fish <- kf_fish %>% column_to_rownames("name")
kf_env <- kf_env %>% column_to_rownames("name") %>% select(!region)

examine richness and diversity

# kf fish richness
kf_sppr <- specnumber(kf_fish)

# difference in richness between regions?
kf_sppr_aov <- aov(kf_sppr ~ region, data = kf_md)
summary(kf_sppr_aov) # no diff
##             Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)
## region       3  327.7  109.23    1.21  0.323
## Residuals   31 2799.0   90.29
# kf fish diversity
kf_shan <- diversity(kf_fish)

# difference in diversity between regions?
kf_shan_aov <- aov(kf_shan ~ region, data = kf_md)
summary(kf_shan_aov) # no diff
##             Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)
## region       3 0.0342 0.01141   0.949  0.429
## Residuals   31 0.3725 0.01202
# difference in species composition between regions?
kf_perm <- adonis2(kf_fish ~ region, data = kf_md)
kf_perm # no diff
## Permutation test for adonis under reduced model
## Terms added sequentially (first to last)
## Permutation: free
## Number of permutations: 999
## 
## adonis2(formula = kf_fish ~ region, data = kf_md)
##          Df SumOfSqs      R2      F Pr(>F)
## region    3  0.15698 0.06418 0.7087  0.636
## Residual 31  2.28887 0.93582              
## Total    34  2.44584 1.00000

nmds

# nmds of fish community
kf_mds <- metaMDS(kf_fish, distance = "euclidean", trymax = 999)
## Wisconsin double standardization
## Run 0 stress 0.03370521 
## Run 1 stress 0.03423796 
## Run 2 stress 0.04969417 
## Run 3 stress 0.0341762 
## ... Procrustes: rmse 0.01545969  max resid 0.05798131

## Run 5 stress 0.03370996 
## ... Procrustes: rmse 0.001180629  max resid 0.005843883 
## ... Similar to previous best
## Run 6 stress 0.0497081 
## Run 7 stress 0.0365562 
## Run 8 stress 0.03415683 
## ... Procrustes: rmse 0.01652518  max resid 0.05631934 
## Run 9 stress 0.03372954 
## ... Procrustes: rmse 0.00335581  max resid 0.01659134 
## Run 10 stress 0.03415677 
## ... Procrustes: rmse 0.01614444  max resid 0.05681031 
## Run 11 stress 0.3427891 
## Run 12 stress 0.03418947 
## ... Procrustes: rmse 0.01528933  max resid 0.05851728 
## Run 13 stress 0.03623107 
## Run 14 stress 0.03555732 
## Run 15 stress 0.0337204 
## ... Procrustes: rmse 0.002135969  max resid 0.01056576 
## Run 16 stress 0.03415753 
## ... Procrustes: rmse 0.01606412  max resid 0.05695924 
## Run 17 stress 0.03654606 
## Run 18 stress 0.03373551 
## ... Procrustes: rmse 0.003794912  max resid 0.018753 
## Run 19 stress 0.03580253 
## Run 20 stress 0.03658666 
## *** Solution reached
kf_mds
## 
## Call:
## metaMDS(comm = kf_fish, distance = "euclidean", trymax = 999) 
## 
## global Multidimensional Scaling using monoMDS
## 
## Data:     wisconsin(kf_fish) 
## Distance: euclidean 
## 
## Dimensions: 2 
## Stress:     0.03370521 
## Stress type 1, weak ties
## Two convergent solutions found after 20 tries
## Scaling: centring, PC rotation 
## Species: expanded scores based on 'wisconsin(kf_fish)'
stressplot(kf_mds)

# plot nmds of fish community
kf_df <- scores(kf_mds, display = "sites") %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  rownames_to_column("name") %>% 
  full_join(kf_md, by = "name")

kf_plot <- ggplot(kf_df,
                  aes(x = NMDS1, y = NMDS2,
                      color = region, shape = region)) +
  geom_point(size = 3, alpha = 0.5) +
  labs(title = "KF Fish NMDS") + 
  theme_classic()
kf_plot

envfit: species driving separation?

# envfit - how do species contribute to dissimilarity
kf_fit <- envfit(kf_mds, kf_fish, perm = 999)

kf_fit_pvals <- kf_fit$vectors$pvals %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  rownames_to_column("species") %>% 
  dplyr::rename("pvals" = ".") # over half of them have = 0.001

bioenv: link environmental variables to community dissimilarity

# bioenv how do env vars contribute to dissimilarity
kf_bioenv <- bioenv(comm = kf_fish, env = kf_env)
## 1048575 possible subsets (this may take time...)
kf_bioenv
## 
## Call:
## bioenv(comm = kf_fish, env = kf_env) 
## 
## Subset of environmental variables with best correlation to community data.
## 
## Correlations:    spearman 
## Dissimilarities: bray 
## Metric:          euclidean 
## 
## Best model has 9 parameters (max. 20 allowed):
## sandy_beach_km rocky_inter_km max_kelp_canopy_cdfw_km2 soft_substrate_0_30m_km2_comb soft_substrate_200_3000m_km2 submarine_canyon_0_30m_km2 surfgrass_km eelgrass_km2 coastal_marsh_km2
## with correlation  0.2752734
# select best model
kf_model <- kf_bioenv$models[[kf_bioenv$whichbest]] 
kf_keep <- kf_model$best

# use envfit to get vectors for top model variables
kf_envfit <- envfit(kf_mds, kf_env[, kf_keep], perm = 999, na.rm = TRUE)

# extract coordinates for each attribute
kf_envfit_coords <- kf_envfit %>% 
  scores(., display = "vectors") %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  rownames_to_column("attribute")%>% 
  mutate(att.label = c("beach", "rocky intertidal", "kelp", "hard 0-30", "soft 0-30",
                       "soft 200-3000", "canyon 0-30", "surfgrass", "eelgrass"))

# plot
ggplot(kf_df, aes(x = NMDS1, y = NMDS2)) +
  coord_fixed() +
  geom_point(aes(color = region,
                 shape = region),
             size = 3, alpha = 0.8) +
  geom_segment(data = kf_envfit_coords, 
               aes(x = 0, xend = NMDS1,
                   y = 0, yend = NMDS2),
               arrow = arrow(length = unit(0.15, "cm")),
               col = "black") +
  geom_text(data = kf_envfit_coords, 
            aes(label = att.label), 
            size = 2.5) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = c(0), color = "grey70", linetype = 2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = c(0), color = "grey70", linetype = 2) +
  labs(title = "KF Fish",
       color = "",
       shape = "") + 
  theme_classic()
